11:31.398 --> 11:32.899
and all that, that was his deal.

11:32.901 --> 11:35.572
That's why it worked, 'cause it was his.

11:35.574 --> 11:38.243
I gotta find my own thing.

11:38.245 --> 11:41.851
People need a morning circle, Bill.

11:41.853 --> 11:44.355
[Reg] <i>It doesn't... it
doesn't bother me that, um,</i>

11:44.357 --> 11:46.994
people disperse the
moment I arrive, you know?

11:46.996 --> 11:48.363
[clears throat]

11:48.365 --> 11:50.133
I prefer hominy grits.

11:50.135 --> 11:53.139
Our neighbor used to make us grits,

11:53.141 --> 11:56.814
and they would soak
the corn in something...

11:56.816 --> 11:59.453
Oh, um, I've been meaning
to ask you something.

11:59.455 --> 12:02.057
- Lye.
- Hmm?

12:02.059 --> 12:03.260
They would soak the corn in lye.

12:03.262 --> 12:04.596
Hmm?

12:04.598 --> 12:05.798
The kernel would swell

12:05.800 --> 12:07.636
to twice of its original size.

12:07.638 --> 12:09.840
What made you come back?

12:09.842 --> 12:14.852
<i>♪♪♪</i>

12:16.522 --> 12:19.593
I don't know.

12:19.595 --> 12:22.532
Was it something specific that I said,

12:22.534 --> 12:24.937
or... or was it, um, more the fact

12:24.939 --> 12:27.107
that I just spoke to you at all?

12:27.109 --> 12:28.945
You think I came back because of you?

12:28.947 --> 12:30.682
If you want, you can ask me
later, 'cause I'm gonna be,

12:30.684 --> 12:32.384
um, here all day collecting information.

12:32.386 --> 12:35.357
Wow.

12:35.359 --> 12:36.794
- Wow.
- Okay.

12:36.796 --> 12:39.198
To be continued.

12:39.200 --> 12:44.208
<i>♪♪♪</i>

12:44.210 --> 12:46.847
Yo, West Coast, let's just hold fingertips.

12:46.849 --> 12:48.985
[Bill] Okay, people!

12:48.987 --> 12:50.053
Morning.

12:50.055 --> 12:52.692
This is Memphis.

12:52.694 --> 12:56.165
So I'll just go ahead and say the word.

12:56.167 --> 12:58.103
- Elvis.
- Whoo!

12:58.105 --> 13:00.877
All right. The King.

13:03.448 --> 13:07.555
Now, my own fascination
with Elvis is very specific.

13:07.557 --> 13:09.726
It's the Tiki Room Elvis.

13:09.728 --> 13:12.832
It's the live at Graceland album Elvis.

13:12.834 --> 13:15.003
It's the going to see "Magnum Force"

13:15.005 --> 13:18.076
at the Memphian at midnight
with Ginger Alden Elvis.

13:18.078 --> 13:20.915
It's the embattled Elvis

13:20.917 --> 13:23.721
during the late-night
set at the Hilton Elvis.

13:23.723 --> 13:25.190
It's the wounded Elvis.

13:25.192 --> 13:27.862
After Elvis, "What Happened," Elvis?

13:27.864 --> 13:31.004
Disoriented, lonely.

13:32.440 --> 13:36.549
It's the troubled, epic Elvis.

13:38.886 --> 13:41.122
So a moment of silence.

13:41.124 --> 13:43.627
[hushed chatter]

13:43.629 --> 13:46.101
- [cell phone vibrates]
- [man clears throat]

13:47.303 --> 13:49.305
[mouthing words]

13:49.307 --> 13:51.442
But, hey, let's, uh,

13:51.444 --> 13:54.716
let's talk about Alex Chilton
and the Box Tops, right?

13:54.718 --> 13:56.954
Earnestine and Hazel's.

13:56.956 --> 14:00.327
The Peabody Hotel with those little ducks

14:00.329 --> 14:03.333
that wander across the lobby there.

14:03.335 --> 14:04.905
Can you feel it?

14:06.675 --> 14:10.748
So... our circle's gotten a little smaller

14:10.750 --> 14:14.923
these past few days, yes,
but though less in number...

14:14.925 --> 14:17.795
Fewer in number or less in number?

14:17.797 --> 14:19.466
M-my... my dad would know that.

14:19.468 --> 14:22.237
He was... he was a real
stickler for, uh, grammar

14:22.239 --> 14:24.108
and things like that.

14:24.110 --> 14:27.247
Anyhow, I'm gonna get better at this, so...

14:27.249 --> 14:28.951
- [all] Hey...
- Bill, Bill, remember that...

14:28.953 --> 14:30.320
- Oh, hold that. Sorry.
- ...um, thing I asked you?

14:30.322 --> 14:31.757
- Dude!
- Talk about those interviews.

14:31.759 --> 14:32.892
- Talk about those interviews.
- Got it!

14:32.894 --> 14:34.563
- Yeah.
- Pardon me, guys.

14:34.565 --> 14:37.301
Uh, Reg here requests a
few moments of your time.

14:37.303 --> 14:41.476
But, uh, listen, I-I just
want to say thank you and, um,

14:41.478 --> 14:43.012
- it's gonna be a good day.
- [radio chatter]

14:43.014 --> 14:44.583
- We'll, um...
- Cheers, Bill, thanks.

14:44.585 --> 14:46.252
- He kind of...
- Hey.

14:46.254 --> 14:48.256
- ...came at a crucial time.
- Bill, we have proof.

14:48.258 --> 14:50.160
Video surveillance
footage from Little Rock.

14:50.162 --> 14:51.429
It was The Head and The Heart.

14:51.431 --> 14:52.632
Check it out.

14:52.634 --> 14:53.801
<i>[light rock music]</i>

14:53.803 --> 14:55.538
<i>♪ In my waxed up hair... ♪</i>

14:55.540 --> 14:57.809
Bill, if you don't ax this
motherfucking opening act

14:57.811 --> 14:59.345
right now, I am so ready to do it.

14:59.347 --> 15:01.650
Hey, look, I can't find
a replacement by tonight.

15:01.652 --> 15:03.119
- Do you understand?
- Yes, you could,

15:03.121 --> 15:04.990
if you would just ask for help.

15:04.992 --> 15:09.768
Okay, well, just let... let
me handle this in my own way.

15:10.937 --> 15:13.239
<i>♪ Playing at the talent show ♪</i>

15:13.241 --> 15:18.251
<i>♪♪♪</i>

15:19.488 --> 15:21.122
<i>♪ Well, we got our guitars ♪</i>

15:21.124 --> 15:22.759
<i>♪ And we got our thumb picks ♪</i>

15:22.761 --> 15:24.629
<i>♪ And we go on after some... ♪</i>

15:24.631 --> 15:26.867
I love you.

15:26.869 --> 15:28.671
Are you Daddy's girl?

15:28.673 --> 15:29.973
Yeah. [laughs]

15:29.975 --> 15:31.777
Okay, Delores, now put the baby on.

15:31.779 --> 15:34.181
- [baby] <i>Hi, Daddy!</i>
- Hey, baby!

15:34.183 --> 15:36.018
- Ah... ugh.
- [baby] <i>I watch the video.</i>

15:36.020 --> 15:37.557
- Later.
- [baby] <i>I miss y...</i>

15:40.395 --> 15:43.132
I think you know why I'm here.

15:43.134 --> 15:47.407
Look, I had zero involvement
in Phil's Katrina thing.

15:47.409 --> 15:49.044
The minute I discovered
the defrauding, pfft,

15:49.046 --> 15:50.848
I blew the whistle.

15:50.850 --> 15:52.652
Okay, I was involved for a minute.

15:52.654 --> 15:54.421
I-I admit it.

15:54.423 --> 15:57.060
Easy money. Victimless crime.

15:57.062 --> 16:00.233
Okay, they were victims, but
of really bad weather, not me.

16:00.235 --> 16:02.304
And then I came to my senses... [chuckles]

16:02.306 --> 16:05.176
...after my wife threatened to leave me.

16:05.178 --> 16:07.815
Risking my life, I might add,

16:07.817 --> 16:12.492
because in the past, Phil
has killed two people.

16:12.494 --> 16:14.996
On purpose! You ever look in his eyes?

16:14.998 --> 16:18.169
He's got those killer whale
eyes, right before they lose it

16:18.171 --> 16:19.973
and eat they Sea World trainer.

16:19.975 --> 16:22.678
I mean, if Phil were to
find out I turned him in?

16:22.680 --> 16:24.214
What?

16:24.216 --> 16:27.822
I worked so hard to get
to a band of this level.

16:27.824 --> 16:31.162
If you let me go, I'm not
going back to my old level.

16:31.164 --> 16:33.266
I won't have a level. I'll be level-less.

16:33.268 --> 16:34.401
Harvey, I'm not here to fire you.

16:34.403 --> 16:35.871
I just need to borrow your office.

16:35.873 --> 16:38.276
The one they gave me
smells, but thanks for that.

16:38.278 --> 16:40.447
Oh. [chuckles]

16:40.449 --> 16:43.887
- Thank God.
- But...

16:43.889 --> 16:47.227
...I do expect your support.

16:47.229 --> 16:48.396
And loyalty.

16:48.398 --> 16:50.768
Of course! Of...

16:50.770 --> 16:53.139
man, I'm loyal as hell
when I'm not snitching.

16:53.141 --> 16:54.476
Ha, I'm your dude.

16:54.478 --> 16:56.646
And thank you.

16:56.648 --> 16:58.884
- Can I hug you?
- Absolutely not.

16:58.886 --> 17:01.823
<i>[blues music]</i>

17:01.825 --> 17:05.664
<i>♪♪♪</i>

17:05.665 --> 17:07.737
[sighs]

17:10.442 --> 17:11.843
Look, you're just gonna have to let people

17:11.845 --> 17:13.012
feel this way for a while.

17:13.013 --> 17:14.582
What? What way?

17:14.584 --> 17:16.520
People are pissed at you 'cause you left.

17:16.521 --> 17:19.526
Remember when Mom and
Dad left, how we felt?

17:19.528 --> 17:22.030
See, this is why I can't be around you.

17:22.031 --> 17:23.700
And you can't demand a nickname.

17:23.702 --> 17:25.905
That shit's, like, bestowed.

17:25.906 --> 17:29.278
You gotta let people know,
"Hey, I'm back, for real.

17:29.280 --> 17:31.081
You can count on me."

17:31.083 --> 17:35.156
I don't need your help, okay?

17:35.158 --> 17:37.995
And Mom would never
have left if Dad hadn't.

17:37.997 --> 17:40.168
What is Winston doing?

17:43.676 --> 17:45.978
- Coloring.
- With your balisong knife?

17:45.980 --> 17:47.682
Yeah.

17:47.684 --> 17:49.117
You provided him with a weapon.

17:49.119 --> 17:50.487
Ah, it's a loan.

17:50.489 --> 17:52.491
You should not be supervising a child.

17:52.493 --> 17:54.328
You should not have jumped onto my tour.

17:54.330 --> 17:55.464
I had to!

17:55.466 --> 17:56.466
I can't be at home,

17:56.468 --> 17:58.269
be around my home friends.

17:58.271 --> 18:00.306
I don't get their lives and
they don't get mine either.

18:00.308 --> 18:02.912
Plus all the mail, trying
to decide what to eat,

18:02.914 --> 18:04.482
it just get... oh, God!

18:04.484 --> 18:07.420
It's just... it's really hard being you.

18:07.422 --> 18:08.890
It gets to me.

18:08.892 --> 18:10.326
- You know what, Wes?
- What?

18:10.328 --> 18:11.663
He's armed.

18:11.665 --> 18:13.834
Oh, Christ on a bike! Hey!

18:13.836 --> 18:15.904
Get back here, devil child!

18:15.906 --> 18:17.073
[Shelli] Ugh, fuck! Shit!

18:17.075 --> 18:19.779
There is no fucking reception here.

18:19.781 --> 18:22.652
- Uh, um...
- What?

18:22.654 --> 18:24.421
...no, nothing.

18:24.423 --> 18:28.162
Just, um...

18:28.164 --> 18:30.768
...I'm back, for real.

18:30.770 --> 18:33.507
You can count on me, okay?

18:33.509 --> 18:36.680
Okay, yeah. Good.

18:36.682 --> 18:38.884
- You'll run the teleprompter.
- What?

18:38.886 --> 18:40.988
Tom Staton requested a teleprompter.

18:40.990 --> 18:42.692
- You get to run it.
- [groans]

18:42.694 --> 18:45.497
- [cell phone vibrates]
- Yeah, this is Shelli.

18:45.499 --> 18:47.167
A teleprompter?

18:47.169 --> 18:48.970
You want me to explain what I do?

18:48.972 --> 18:52.478
The first band I ever worked
for cried when I left them.

18:52.480 --> 18:54.247
I don't have to prove myself to you.

18:54.249 --> 18:57.053
Do you know how many times a
day one of those local union guys

18:57.055 --> 18:59.692
asks me who in the band is my boyfriend,

18:59.694 --> 19:01.763
or if I know what all
those little knobs do,

19:01.765 --> 19:04.000
or where the sound <i>man</i> is?

19:04.002 --> 19:06.271
Nobody has a thicker skin than me.

19:06.273 --> 19:08.777
My girlfriend is pregnant, and I love her,

19:08.779 --> 19:11.381
but she will never understand what I do.

19:11.383 --> 19:15.791
My girlfriend, who makes
me come without touching me,

19:15.793 --> 19:17.628
will never really get it.

19:17.630 --> 19:21.669
So do you think you'll ever grasp it?

19:21.671 --> 19:23.874
And you are Donna.

19:23.876 --> 19:26.880
<i>[electronic pop music]</i>

19:26.882 --> 19:28.349
<i>♪♪♪</i>

19:28.351 --> 19:30.219
Hello, Head and The Heart.

19:30.221 --> 19:33.560
You look good. Yeah.

19:33.562 --> 19:36.533
You know, Coach John Wooden once said,

19:36.535 --> 19:41.041
"98% of who we are is
equal to every other person.

19:41.043 --> 19:44.949
It's what you do with that extra 2%."

19:44.951 --> 19:48.757
Now, your great band is at a crossroads.

19:48.759 --> 19:52.263
So you can use your 2% for antagonism,

19:52.265 --> 19:55.938
or you can use your 2%
to join our community,

19:55.940 --> 19:59.211
or you can continue to fuck with us,

19:59.213 --> 20:02.317
and we'll ask you to leave this tour.

20:02.319 --> 20:06.459
And that is the story of
how malcontents are born.

20:06.461 --> 20:09.932
Now, I-I-I think we got
off on the wrong foot,

20:09.934 --> 20:13.005
so let's change shoes.

20:13.007 --> 20:15.744
My dad taught me that. He was a shoe guy.

20:15.746 --> 20:18.516
Let's take the next step together.

20:18.518 --> 20:20.487
Let's... let's exercise together.

20:20.489 --> 20:22.423
Let's drink Bullet Coffees together.

20:22.425 --> 20:26.799
Coach Wooden, he also
said, "Failure is not fatal.

20:26.801 --> 20:30.474
Failure to change might be."

20:30.476 --> 20:31.976
Gentlemen and ladies,

20:31.978 --> 20:34.147
this is a holy endeavor.

20:34.149 --> 20:37.353
<i>♪♪♪</i>

20:37.355 --> 20:39.291
Thanks.

20:39.293 --> 20:41.796
<i>♪♪♪</i>

20:41.798 --> 20:45.136
I-I-I-I got to admit,
I-I was magnificent.

20:45.138 --> 20:47.407
I found a groove and I talked with them,

20:47.409 --> 20:48.843
you know, not at them.

20:48.845 --> 20:50.714
Eh, you can see how these cult leaders

20:50.716 --> 20:52.685
and televangelists, how they
could get carried away...

20:52.687 --> 20:54.822
- They just quit.
- What?

20:54.824 --> 20:56.693
Yeah, they're taking the
Neil Young dates in Europe.

20:56.695 --> 20:59.097
- No! What about...
- We need an opening act.

20:59.099 --> 21:02.170
Well, what about, like,
Coach Wooden and the shoes?

21:02.172 --> 21:03.640
What shoes?

21:03.642 --> 21:06.679
We have less than six
hours to find a replacement.

21:06.681 --> 21:09.785
- Call Phil!
- No! You know, fuck it.

21:09.787 --> 21:13.058
I'll find a goddamn
opening act on my own, okay?

21:13.060 --> 21:14.862
- I-I can't.
- Wait.

21:14.864 --> 21:17.568
[sighs] Where you going?

21:17.570 --> 21:19.905
Shelli for Kelly Ann. Meet me stage left.

21:19.907 --> 21:22.410
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

21:22.412 --> 21:23.682
What?

21:24.684 --> 21:26.488
[groans]

21:28.057 --> 21:30.560
Teleprompters are a snap. You'll be fine.

21:30.562 --> 21:33.666
Just do not look away, even for a second.

21:33.668 --> 21:35.737
I know a girl who did
teleprompter for Sting.

21:35.739 --> 21:37.040
She leaned down to scratch her ankle

21:37.042 --> 21:38.543
in the middle of "Fields of Gold."

21:38.545 --> 21:40.179
The lyrics started scrolling in Spanish.

21:40.181 --> 21:42.116
Sting sang them in Spanish.
<i>"Campos de Oro."</i>

21:42.118 --> 21:43.853
They were in France.

21:43.855 --> 21:46.559
She's in a group home now,
but I will text you her number.

21:46.561 --> 21:48.295
- She'll walk you through it.
- [stammers]

21:48.297 --> 21:50.901
- I'm a rigger. I can't.
- Yes, you can.

21:50.903 --> 21:53.372
You'll do both, plus...

21:53.374 --> 21:56.479
Uh, guys, why the fuck are
the monitors not up yet?

21:56.481 --> 21:58.883
Plus any other crap job I dump on you.

21:58.885 --> 22:01.388
Someone's getting fired
today. Do you get that?

22:01.390 --> 22:02.891
You're not in film school, Dorothy.

22:02.893 --> 22:05.029
Just lose the attitude.

22:05.031 --> 22:06.999
I mean, the fact that they
even need a teleprompter

22:07.001 --> 22:08.736
- is kind of on you.
- What?

22:08.738 --> 22:10.507
Well, you're the one who told
them to change the set list.

22:10.509 --> 22:12.744
I never thought that they would listen.

22:12.746 --> 22:14.849
Just get your ass over to the Peabody.

22:14.851 --> 22:18.355
I'm gonna text you the alias
Christopher's checked in under.

22:18.357 --> 22:20.294
Find out what songs they
want programmed for tonight.

22:25.138 --> 22:26.772
- [sighs]
- Thank you!

22:26.774 --> 22:29.144
Uh, so two cities ago,
uh, the band's stalker

22:29.146 --> 22:30.947
got backstage and firecrackers went off

22:30.949 --> 22:32.416
in the middle of the show.

22:32.418 --> 22:33.920
No, it was in the beginning.

22:33.922 --> 22:35.590
Yeah, no, I-I suppose my point is, Puna,

22:35.592 --> 22:38.763
what exactly is it you do?

22:38.765 --> 22:40.901
I sense.

22:40.903 --> 22:43.473
Oh, I'm... I'm... I'm afraid I'm
gonna need a bit more than that.

22:43.475 --> 22:46.311
I have seen you...

22:46.313 --> 22:47.648
on your way to us.

22:47.650 --> 22:49.317
What, you mean this... this morning?

22:49.319 --> 22:53.025
No. On your way to us.

22:53.027 --> 22:56.131
You were chubby as a young one.

22:56.133 --> 22:59.471
How... how did you know that?

22:59.473 --> 23:01.842
You hate being touched.

23:01.844 --> 23:03.980
I know you are afraid.

23:03.982 --> 23:06.286
I see your fears.

23:10.629 --> 23:13.600
You won't fire me.

23:13.602 --> 23:17.440
And you will face those fears.

23:17.442 --> 23:20.446
<i>[upbeat R&B music]</i>

23:20.448 --> 23:22.016
<i>♪♪♪</i>

23:22.018 --> 23:23.953
It won't happen tonight.

23:23.955 --> 23:27.260
What... what won't ha... what won't happen?

23:27.262 --> 23:28.496
What won't happen?

23:28.498 --> 23:30.332
<i>♪ Bill collectors at my door ♪</i>

23:30.334 --> 23:33.171
<i>♪ What can you do for me? ♪</i>

23:33.173 --> 23:35.309
<i>♪♪♪</i>

23:35.311 --> 23:36.812
- _
- <i>♪ Hey ♪</i>

23:36.814 --> 23:39.217
- _
- <i>♪♪♪</i>

23:39.219 --> 23:40.520
[no audible dialogue]

23:40.522 --> 23:43.726
<i>♪ No romance without finance ♪</i>

23:43.728 --> 23:45.129
[no audible dialogue]

23:45.131 --> 23:49.638
<i>♪ No romance without finance ♪</i>

23:49.640 --> 23:53.713
<i>♪ Boy nothing in life is free ♪</i>

23:53.715 --> 23:55.750
<i>♪ That's why I'm asking you ♪</i>

23:55.752 --> 23:58.221
<i>♪ What can you do for me? ♪</i>

23:58.223 --> 24:01.929
<i>♪ I've got responsibilities ♪</i>

24:01.931 --> 24:04.468
<i>♪ So I'm looking for a man ♪</i>

24:04.470 --> 24:07.774
<i>♪ Who's got some
money in his hands ♪</i>

24:07.776 --> 24:11.982
<i>♪ 'Cause nothing from
nothing leaves nothing ♪</i>

24:11.984 --> 24:15.322
<i>♪ You got to have something
if you wanna be with me ♪</i>

24:15.324 --> 24:17.226
<i>♪ Oh life... ♪</i>

24:17.228 --> 24:21.869
So, uh, Mr. Pigfucker...
tell me about yourself.

24:21.871 --> 24:23.071
Uh, well, I've toured around the world

24:23.073 --> 24:24.808
with, like, 14 different bands.

24:24.810 --> 24:28.415
Um, I make the dankest coffee
you'll probably ever drink.

24:28.417 --> 24:29.985
And when I'm home, I garden.

24:29.987 --> 24:31.989
I-I have a
guitar-shaped garden.

24:31.991 --> 24:33.828
It's called the guitarden.

24:35.565 --> 24:36.732
Guitar and garden.

24:36.734 --> 24:40.038
Uh, and then I nanny this young gem.

24:40.040 --> 24:42.412
So what's your story? [clears throat]

24:44.282 --> 24:47.621
He's got a butterfly knife.

24:47.623 --> 24:49.958
- Oh, yeah, it's coloring time.
- That's highly dangerous.

24:49.960 --> 24:51.194
You know how to work that thing, right?

24:51.196 --> 24:53.866
Show him.

24:53.868 --> 24:56.772
- [Reg] Oh, Jesus.
- [Wesley] Mm-hmm.

24:56.774 --> 24:59.143
Yeah!

24:59.145 --> 25:00.312
Please leave.

25:00.314 --> 25:02.183
Aw, come on.

25:02.185 --> 25:04.488
Thank you.

25:04.490 --> 25:07.359
[ducks quacking]

25:07.361 --> 25:09.397
Oh, may I help you, young lady?

25:09.399 --> 25:11.234
Yeah, I'm here to see a guest.

25:11.236 --> 25:13.940
Uh, Dan Manutsitch.

25:13.942 --> 25:16.411
Manutsitch?

25:16.413 --> 25:17.848
Yeah.

25:17.850 --> 25:19.050
First name?

25:19.052 --> 25:21.421
Uh, Dan.

25:21.423 --> 25:23.960
Last name?

25:23.962 --> 25:26.532
Manutsitch.

25:26.534 --> 25:30.940
Ma... nuts...

25:30.942 --> 25:31.976
...itch.

25:31.978 --> 25:35.082
That... that's the one.

25:35.084 --> 25:36.619
Oh, here it is.

25:36.621 --> 25:37.921
Dan Manutsitch.

25:37.923 --> 25:40.660
Room 720.

25:40.662 --> 25:42.396
[rapid beeping]

25:42.398 --> 25:44.267
How is it?

25:44.269 --> 25:45.670
It's, um...

25:45.672 --> 25:47.172
Ahh.

25:47.174 --> 25:49.176
[exhales deeply]

25:49.178 --> 25:51.482
Huh?

25:51.484 --> 25:54.020
- Is it a good...
- 160 over 103.

25:54.022 --> 25:55.422
Is that good or bad?

25:55.424 --> 25:57.126
- It's not good.
- Fuck me.

25:57.128 --> 26:00.032
Oh, no, no, no. Don't swear.

26:00.034 --> 26:01.835
Okay, and you take good care of yourself.

26:01.837 --> 26:03.038
- Thank you.
- Okay.

26:03.040 --> 26:04.474
- I care about you.
- Thank you.

26:04.476 --> 26:05.777
- All right, honey.
- Okay.

26:05.779 --> 26:07.747
There you go. All right.

26:07.749 --> 26:08.916
[sighs]

26:08.918 --> 26:10.285
- Okay, thank you.
- Okay.

26:10.287 --> 26:12.724
[cell phone rings]

26:12.726 --> 26:14.595
[sighs]

26:14.597 --> 26:17.266
<i>Bill, life is a gym, and
I hear you are having</i>

26:17.268 --> 26:18.903
<i>a hell of a workout.</i>

26:18.905 --> 26:20.740
Hey, Phil. How you doing?

26:20.742 --> 26:22.744
<i>Well, we're up here on
the launchpad in Finland.</i>

26:22.746 --> 26:25.248
<i>Blast off in two days,
and Taylor Swift will be</i>

26:25.250 --> 26:28.188
<i>the first pop star
to perform in space.</i>

26:28.190 --> 26:30.359
<i>"Planet Swift Tour," that's
what we're calling it.</i>

26:30.361 --> 26:32.129
No kidding? Well, I gotta say,

26:32.131 --> 26:34.000
I'm not surprised. She... she deserves

26:34.002 --> 26:35.470
to be the first one up there.

26:35.472 --> 26:37.641
<i>Yes, she does.</i>

26:37.643 --> 26:39.511
That's pretty exciting.

26:39.513 --> 26:41.482
<i>Uh, Sean told me Head and
The Heart quit on you.</i>

26:41.484 --> 26:43.786
They... they did. It was amicable.

26:43.788 --> 26:45.389
<i>Yeah, I still don't trust 'em.</i>

26:45.391 --> 26:46.725
<i>I hadn't trusted a northwest band</i>

26:46.727 --> 26:48.228
<i>since The Kingsmen rendered</i>

26:48.230 --> 26:50.332
<i>two minutes and 40 seconds of heaven</i>

26:50.334 --> 26:52.169
- <i>known as "Louie Louie."</i>
- Right.

26:52.171 --> 26:53.873
<i>I knew you needed a new support act,</i>

26:53.875 --> 26:55.342
<i>and I made some calls for you, Bill.</i>

26:55.344 --> 26:56.979
We... we are looking. Thank you.

26:56.981 --> 26:58.749
<i>I found somebody for you.</i>

26:58.751 --> 26:59.818
No kidding?

26:59.820 --> 27:01.989
<i>Reignwolf.</i>

27:01.991 --> 27:04.093
Great, Phil. Thank you.

27:04.095 --> 27:06.364
Say, uh, Phil, when...

27:06.366 --> 27:08.869
when you used to walk the guys
to the stage, how would you...

27:08.871 --> 27:10.640
<i>Give me a minute. What was that?</i>

27:10.642 --> 27:12.811
Never mind.

27:12.813 --> 27:13.946
Thanks again.

27:13.948 --> 27:15.717
<i>Happy to help, Bill.</i>

27:15.719 --> 27:18.054
<i>And remember, it's
Taylor Swift's world.</i>

27:18.056 --> 27:20.528
<i>She's just letting us sit in it.</i>

27:22.331 --> 27:24.634
Great. [mutters]

27:24.636 --> 27:27.474
Come on, Bill, you got this.

27:27.476 --> 27:29.310
Where is it you're from exactly?

27:29.312 --> 27:31.314
North. The north.

27:31.316 --> 27:33.686
- Near Bristol.
- Near Bristol?

27:33.688 --> 27:35.523
- Actually Bromley.
- Bromley?

27:35.525 --> 27:38.496
Yeah, east side of the
north side of Bromley.

27:38.498 --> 27:40.265
- Near Leamington Spa?
- Yeah.

27:40.267 --> 27:42.236
Leamington Spa meets Bromley. That's right.

27:42.238 --> 27:44.908
Yeah, yeah, Bromley's nowhere
near Leamington Spa or Bristol.

27:44.910 --> 27:48.214
It is, mate, if you travel...
to the west, by the sea.

27:48.216 --> 27:52.457
Look, you are not from England.

27:52.459 --> 27:55.061
You are from New Jersey.

27:55.063 --> 27:57.299
I have your W-2 here.

27:57.301 --> 27:59.236
All right, all right, fine!
Yeah, I admit it, all right?

27:59.238 --> 28:00.740
Look, I toured with Elvis Costello

28:00.742 --> 28:02.042
and... and I can't stop it, you know?

28:02.044 --> 28:03.344
It just happens. It comes out of me mouth.

28:03.346 --> 28:04.180
- It's just all...
- Okay, enough.

28:04.182 --> 28:05.348
Enough! Enough!

28:05.350 --> 28:07.854
Please just give me some idea

28:07.856 --> 28:09.423
of what it is you do.

28:09.425 --> 28:10.827
Pretend I'm an alien.

28:10.829 --> 28:14.534
Explain to me what you do.

28:14.536 --> 28:17.105
I protect the bass, I fix broken things,

28:17.107 --> 28:19.511
and I owe a cruel obedience to anarchy.

28:19.513 --> 28:21.949
Right. Listen.

28:21.951 --> 28:25.590
Lose the offensive accent, or you're out.

28:25.592 --> 28:27.292
[American accent] What accent?

28:27.294 --> 28:29.731
Okay. Terrific.

28:29.733 --> 28:31.300
- Great.
- Thanks for your time.

28:31.302 --> 28:32.871
- Do I still have my job?
- Thanks very much.

28:32.873 --> 28:33.973
- Great.
- Thank you.

28:33.975 --> 28:35.576
Thank you. [clears throat]

28:35.578 --> 28:37.312
- Do you want it open or closed?
- Closed, please.

28:37.314 --> 28:39.484
Closed, okay.

28:39.486 --> 28:40.820
[door closes]

28:40.822 --> 28:42.389
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

28:42.391 --> 28:44.426
Wesley, stop blowing up my phone

28:44.428 --> 28:46.732
asking me if I've seen
Winston or your fucking knife.

28:46.734 --> 28:48.469
I'm about to see Christopher fucking House,

28:48.471 --> 28:50.005
who intimidates the shit out of me,

28:50.007 --> 28:51.975
to talk to him about the
stupid fucking teleprompter,

28:51.977 --> 28:54.581
to which I am morally opposed
but apparently is now my job.

28:54.583 --> 28:56.752
As opposed to you making
friends and coffee,

28:56.754 --> 28:58.622
I am sleep deprived and
I realize I have made

28:58.624 --> 28:59.991
a huge fucking mistake.

28:59.993 --> 29:01.795
I should have just quit since clearly

29:01.797 --> 29:03.264
nobody wants me to be here.

29:03.266 --> 29:05.302
And Spike Lee is leaving
me automated messages

29:05.304 --> 29:07.807
telling me how happy he is that
I'm going to NYU film school.

29:07.809 --> 29:09.276
But it's all good.

29:09.278 --> 29:10.412
I'll probably end up being the one

29:10.414 --> 29:11.548
who gets fired today.

29:11.550 --> 29:14.487
Wish me luck.

29:14.489 --> 29:16.725
[elevator bell rings]

29:16.727 --> 29:18.963
Can you come with me this way?

29:18.965 --> 29:20.800
Kelly Ann is here for you.

29:20.802 --> 29:23.071
You can have a seat right there.

29:23.073 --> 29:24.975
<i>♪♪♪</i>

29:24.977 --> 29:26.480
Oh, "Dead Sex."

29:28.083 --> 29:31.155
Everybody watches it on
the bus except for me.

29:37.167 --> 29:39.269
- "Why are you here?"
- To ask you which songs

29:39.271 --> 29:40.840
you want to have on the teleprompter.

29:40.842 --> 29:42.643
"'Why are you here?' she cried,

29:42.645 --> 29:45.015
and in that moment, I died.

29:45.017 --> 29:46.451
To see her giving.

29:46.453 --> 29:50.559
A death worth living."

29:50.561 --> 29:53.064
That's amazing. Yeah.

29:53.066 --> 29:55.201
[scoffs]

29:55.203 --> 29:56.838
Anyway, I don't want anything

29:56.840 --> 29:58.241
on the fucking teleprompter, okay?

29:58.243 --> 29:59.844
Tom's the one who wants it.

29:59.846 --> 30:01.815
He's got lead singer shit to worry about.

30:01.817 --> 30:05.523
And I'm at least ten years
away from "Stage-heimer's."

30:05.525 --> 30:08.161
I'm sorry. Um...

30:08.163 --> 30:11.902
...so how's everyone
feeling about all the changes

30:11.904 --> 30:13.605
and the British guy?

30:13.607 --> 30:15.275
[clicks tongue]

30:15.277 --> 30:17.079
Uh, they're kind of upset.

30:17.081 --> 30:20.353
I didn't know he was gonna fire people.

30:22.257 --> 30:24.527
- Do you want some raisins?
- No, thanks.

30:24.529 --> 30:27.299
Not a fan of raisins, which is strange

30:27.301 --> 30:29.269
'cause usually I'll eat anything,

30:29.271 --> 30:31.407
but a raisin is essentially a person's idea

30:31.409 --> 30:35.315
of how to change a grape when
a grape was already perfect.

30:35.317 --> 30:36.885
- Wow.
- And philosophically,

30:36.887 --> 30:39.089
I hate how people add raisins

30:39.091 --> 30:40.258
where they do not belong.

30:40.260 --> 30:42.295
Stuffing, Cream of Wheat, salad.

30:42.297 --> 30:43.899
When will people learn

30:43.901 --> 30:46.938
that raisins are not always the answer?

30:46.940 --> 30:48.642
You're right.

30:48.644 --> 30:51.080
We gotta get rid of Reg.

30:51.082 --> 30:52.650
- Pardon me?
- I get it.

30:52.652 --> 30:54.487
- You're talking in metaphor.
- No, no, no.

30:54.489 --> 30:56.123
I was talking about actual raisins.

30:56.125 --> 30:58.161
Well, it was incredibly meaningful to me.

30:58.163 --> 31:00.666
Uh, which, uh, songs would you like

31:00.668 --> 31:01.601
to have on the teleprompter?

31:01.603 --> 31:03.705
I haven't decided.

31:03.707 --> 31:07.647
I feel this freedom to not have a plan

31:07.649 --> 31:09.984
ever since you said that thing
about changing the set list.

31:09.986 --> 31:12.490
- But...
- You have a gift, Kelly Ann,

31:12.492 --> 31:14.092
for saying what needs to be said.

31:14.094 --> 31:18.067
No. I just talk a lot,

31:18.069 --> 31:20.438
and I was talking about the raisins.

31:20.440 --> 31:21.641
No, you weren't.

31:21.643 --> 31:23.344
He's got an appointment right now,

31:23.346 --> 31:24.614
so you can actually get going.

31:24.616 --> 31:25.783
Sure. [laughs]

31:25.785 --> 31:27.453
I... but I was actually talking

31:27.455 --> 31:30.492
about... about the raisins.

31:30.494 --> 31:32.697
Just, uh, ra... raisins, for sure.

31:32.699 --> 31:33.634
Okay. [chuckles]

31:34.970 --> 31:37.540
So you're... you're the tour manager.

31:37.542 --> 31:39.510
Oh, no, no, no. Bill is the tour manager.

31:39.512 --> 31:41.313
I'm the production manager.

31:41.315 --> 31:43.217
But Bill, uh, started doing merch.

31:43.219 --> 31:44.654
He goes all the way back with this band

31:44.656 --> 31:46.156
from before the beginning.

31:46.158 --> 31:48.194
He and Christopher were
friends, uh, you know,

31:48.196 --> 31:49.664
since... since the eighth grade.

31:49.666 --> 31:52.637
Ah, so... could it be possible

31:52.639 --> 31:55.743
that because he works for his friend,

31:55.745 --> 32:00.753
that Bill could be, um...

32:00.755 --> 32:02.657
- ...coasting?
- Well, that's fucking bullshit.

32:02.659 --> 32:03.659
- No, I...
- No, no, no.

32:03.661 --> 32:05.094
Bill barely sleeps.

32:05.096 --> 32:07.466
This... this is a person with integrity.

32:07.468 --> 32:10.338
I mean, sure, he's unaware of it and...

32:10.340 --> 32:13.177
[sighs] ...he hits on women half his age

32:13.179 --> 32:17.787
in a way that's borderline
illegal and just sad to me,

32:17.789 --> 32:20.559
but, um... look.

32:20.561 --> 32:23.397
I suck at compliments, but this is a guy

32:23.399 --> 32:26.070
who reads Coach John Wooden's
book before he goes to sleep

32:26.072 --> 32:29.142
because it's the one thing
his fucking fiasco of a father

32:29.144 --> 32:33.017
ever gave him.

32:33.019 --> 32:37.192
Next question.

32:37.194 --> 32:39.196
I think we're good.

32:39.198 --> 32:41.668
[man] <i>Just so everyone's
clear, tonight's opening act</i>

32:41.670 --> 32:44.776
<i>is going to be Reignwolf and
not The Head and The Heart.</i>

32:46.847 --> 32:50.351
[Shelli] Hey, thought I
might find you up here.

32:50.353 --> 32:53.525
So, Reignwolf. Saving our ass.

32:53.527 --> 32:55.128
- Yup.
- [chuckles]

32:55.130 --> 32:57.365
That's Phil's idea.

32:57.367 --> 33:00.873
Talk to Christopher
about kissing his fingers?

33:00.875 --> 33:02.142
I mean, they're so close.

33:02.144 --> 33:03.879
Why can't Tom just tell him himself?

33:03.881 --> 33:05.516
Why can't they just talk about it?

33:05.518 --> 33:07.486
I guess there's just some things people,

33:07.488 --> 33:08.822
you know, don't know how to say.

33:08.824 --> 33:10.492
Gotta do it quick like ripping off a...

33:10.494 --> 33:13.665
I can't believe you
called Phil behind my back.

33:13.667 --> 33:14.767
I-I didn't.

33:14.769 --> 33:16.270
No, you called your husband

33:16.272 --> 33:19.176
who works with Phil.

33:19.178 --> 33:20.546
Bill, I was trying to help.

33:20.548 --> 33:23.518
I-I don't want that kind of help.

33:23.520 --> 33:26.458
Hey, you think just
'cause Sean is on retainer

33:26.460 --> 33:29.396
with Taylor Swift, I'm
sitting in a tub of butter?

33:29.398 --> 33:31.701
We keep our money separate,
and my mother needs a new roof

33:31.703 --> 33:33.103
and both knees replaced.

33:33.105 --> 33:34.941
My medusa of a sister is no help at all.

33:34.943 --> 33:36.210
It all lands on me.

33:36.212 --> 33:38.047
And if this tour goes all to hell,

33:38.049 --> 33:39.249
who's getting fired?

33:39.251 --> 33:40.552
Christopher House's oldest friend?

33:40.554 --> 33:42.756
Probably not.

33:42.758 --> 33:44.392
"Sitting in a tub of butter"?

33:44.394 --> 33:46.096
- Pe... people say that?
- Yes.

33:46.098 --> 33:47.500
I've got it! Why has this band

33:47.502 --> 33:48.969
never released a box set?

33:48.971 --> 33:52.576
Extra content, preexisting valuable stuff,

33:52.578 --> 33:57.586
that is the way to energize
and monetize the fan base.

33:57.588 --> 33:59.824
Right. Well...

33:59.826 --> 34:01.126
Well, I think the thing is, Reg...

34:01.128 --> 34:02.362
- Mmm.
- ...nobody in the band

34:02.364 --> 34:03.532
saved anything.

34:03.534 --> 34:04.534
Yeah, there... there's no collector

34:04.536 --> 34:05.769
in this band.

34:05.771 --> 34:07.740
[Bill] There's no extra material.

34:07.742 --> 34:09.376
[man] <i>Jordan Cook just
checked in backstage.</i>

34:09.378 --> 34:11.246
Reignwolf is in the building.

34:11.248 --> 34:13.050
But I-I do have a suggestion

34:13.052 --> 34:15.556
if you're concerned about the brand.

34:15.558 --> 34:16.824
You know I am.

34:16.826 --> 34:18.594
It concerns Christopher.

34:18.597 --> 34:20.966
You know the thing he
does, you know, with...

34:20.967 --> 34:22.770
...kissing his fingertips?

34:22.772 --> 34:26.476
It... you know, sadly, they're
mocking it on social media, Reg.

34:26.478 --> 34:28.347
- [Reg] Are they?
- [Bill] Yes, they are.

34:28.349 --> 34:30.953
And, you know, somebody really
needs to say something to him,

34:30.955 --> 34:34.827
because, between you and me, Tom hates it.

34:34.829 --> 34:36.598
And this is exactly the kind of thing

34:36.600 --> 34:38.702
that can, you know, pull a band apart.

34:38.704 --> 34:41.139
[Reg] Well, Christopher has
just asked to, uh, see me.

34:41.141 --> 34:43.344
I was gonna ask you if you
knew what that was about.

34:43.346 --> 34:46.884
I-I don't, but, you know,
what a great opportunity

34:46.886 --> 34:50.056
to... help the brand.

34:50.059 --> 34:52.061
[man] <i>Christopher is asking for Reg,</i>

34:52.063 --> 34:54.500
<i>and Reignwolf is
ready for soundcheck.</i>

34:54.502 --> 34:56.638
[guitar chords strumming]

34:56.639 --> 34:59.710
Can I get a little bit more, uh, monitor?

34:59.712 --> 35:01.848
Turn... turn the guitar, I would say.

35:01.850 --> 35:03.952
It's loud there.

35:03.954 --> 35:06.089
Uh, here's what we're gonna do.

35:06.091 --> 35:09.195
Just for tonight, I think,
uh, it'd be badass if...

35:09.197 --> 35:11.868
bring that over here, uh, the drum.

35:11.870 --> 35:13.938
And I... can I bring you up a bit?

35:13.940 --> 35:16.511
If we did it more of a, like, a broke...

35:16.513 --> 35:18.515
a brokedown kind of...

35:18.517 --> 35:21.521
[band plays slow blues]

35:21.523 --> 35:26.533
<i>♪♪♪</i>

35:29.539 --> 35:31.841
I'll go like this. Ah!

35:31.843 --> 35:35.414
<i>♪ Let's not get lost
in the deep end ♪</i>

35:35.416 --> 35:38.688
<i>♪♪♪</i>

35:38.690 --> 35:42.228
<i>♪ Not when I'm
catching my breath ♪</i>

35:42.230 --> 35:43.598
Uh...

35:43.600 --> 35:45.836
<i>♪♪♪</i>

35:45.838 --> 35:50.411
<i>♪ And I don't want
to do this anymore ♪</i>

35:50.413 --> 35:52.950
<i>♪ I'm always saying ♪</i>

35:52.952 --> 35:57.926
<i>♪ You keep trying to
break down my wall ♪</i>

35:57.928 --> 36:00.264
<i>♪ You just think you're ♪</i>

36:00.266 --> 36:03.571
<i>♪ Hardcore ♪</i>

