37:50.787 --> 37:52.622
Jesus Christ.

37:52.624 --> 37:53.891
[cheers and applause]

37:53.893 --> 37:55.895
[sighs]

37:55.897 --> 37:58.835
Jordan, great job.

37:58.837 --> 38:01.072
Look, I can't tell you how relieved I am.

38:01.074 --> 38:04.178
I-I actually... I've been
having some health issues,

38:04.180 --> 38:06.751
and... anyways. So glad to have you.

38:06.753 --> 38:09.122
We're gonna have a real
blast these next few weeks.

38:09.124 --> 38:10.257
- Thank you.
- Oh, Phil didn't tell you?

38:10.259 --> 38:11.660
No.

38:11.662 --> 38:13.196
I'm on my way out to Copenhagen

38:13.198 --> 38:14.800
right after the show tonight.

38:14.802 --> 38:15.935
- Europe?
- Yeah.

38:15.937 --> 38:17.973
- No! No!
- Yeah, man.

38:17.975 --> 38:19.442
Glad I could help out.

38:19.444 --> 38:21.514
Oh, my God.

38:21.516 --> 38:23.183
Fun times, man.

38:23.185 --> 38:25.020
We'll always have tonight.

38:25.022 --> 38:27.959
<i>♪ See the bright
lights of Memphis ♪</i>

38:27.961 --> 38:31.500
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

38:31.502 --> 38:35.174
<i>♪ I got a friend
lives down there ♪</i>

38:35.176 --> 38:38.815
<i>♪♪♪</i>

38:38.817 --> 38:42.556
<i>♪ And I don't know ♪</i>

38:42.558 --> 38:47.566
<i>♪ If I go back again ♪</i>

38:47.568 --> 38:51.540
<i>♪ Giving up is like dying ♪</i>

38:51.542 --> 38:54.680
<i>♪ I get dreams of flying ♪</i>

38:54.682 --> 38:57.084
<i>♪♪♪</i>

38:57.086 --> 38:59.690
Nope, no set list yet, guys.

38:59.692 --> 39:01.594
Kelly Ann, where have you been?

39:01.596 --> 39:03.330
I went to the hotel and Christopher

39:03.332 --> 39:04.900
offered me raisins, and...

39:04.902 --> 39:06.971
Did he tell you which
songs he wants programmed?

39:06.973 --> 39:09.375
No, he says he feels the
freedom not to have a plan.

39:09.377 --> 39:10.979
Oh, fuck that. Okay, I need you to download

39:10.981 --> 39:12.716
everything for the teleprompter.
When I get a set list,

39:12.718 --> 39:14.185
I'll tell you which songs to put on it.

39:14.187 --> 39:15.420
- Thanks. Thank you.
- Don't thank me.

39:15.422 --> 39:16.826
- I don't mean it.
- Good.

39:25.075 --> 39:26.376
Wha... what are you doing in here?

39:26.378 --> 39:27.512
What are you doing in here?

39:27.514 --> 39:29.248
I have to program my teleprompter.

39:29.250 --> 39:30.518
What? In a truck?

39:30.520 --> 39:31.887
'Cause I needed some place private.

39:31.889 --> 39:33.223
These cases are never unloaded. They're...

39:33.225 --> 39:34.560
Your little scheme to get me fired

39:34.562 --> 39:37.766
didn't quite come off.

39:37.768 --> 39:39.302
What are you talking about?

39:39.304 --> 39:42.241
Uh, I convinced them...

39:42.243 --> 39:44.078
...to give me another chance somehow.

39:44.080 --> 39:46.382
I didn't try to get you fired.

39:46.384 --> 39:48.821
And there I was, thinking foolishly

39:48.823 --> 39:53.564
that we had the makings of some
sort of friend... friendship.

39:53.566 --> 39:57.572
I was talking about raisins.

39:57.574 --> 39:59.943
I would never try to get a person fired.

39:59.945 --> 40:01.847
- [scoffs]
- Even you.

40:01.849 --> 40:03.651
Tha... is that how you see me?

40:03.653 --> 40:07.124
As someone who would try to get you fired?

40:07.126 --> 40:08.928
Why?

40:08.930 --> 40:10.665
'Cause I'm wearing this
stupid fucking T-shirt?

40:10.667 --> 40:11.867
I think it's a nice T-shirt.

40:11.869 --> 40:13.938
Yeah, don't take it personally.

40:13.940 --> 40:16.510
- Phil just mattered to people.
- Yeah, I realized that.

40:16.512 --> 40:18.981
- That's why I had them made.
- What?

40:18.983 --> 40:20.885
I believe in creative cost-effective ways

40:20.887 --> 40:25.227
of allowing workers to
express their frustrations.

40:25.229 --> 40:27.732
Are you serious?

40:27.734 --> 40:30.070
Almost always.

40:30.072 --> 40:33.143
Like yourself.

40:33.145 --> 40:36.082
Now, I've told you my secret.

40:36.084 --> 40:38.388
You tell me one.

40:40.259 --> 40:42.361
I have to go. I have to
figure out which songs

40:42.363 --> 40:43.831
they want to have on the teleprompter.

40:43.833 --> 40:46.369
Like, for instance, who
is... who is this, um,

40:46.371 --> 40:49.175
Double D that everyone keeps talking about?

40:49.177 --> 40:50.678
Because I can't seem to find him or her

40:50.680 --> 40:52.348
in any of the paperwork.

40:52.350 --> 40:54.418
- What?
- Um, it's you.

40:54.420 --> 40:55.555
It's your nickname.

40:55.557 --> 40:57.024
Yeah, Double D?

40:57.026 --> 41:00.432
And what... what does it stand for?

41:03.238 --> 41:06.008
Due Diligence.

41:06.010 --> 41:08.014
Really?

41:09.985 --> 41:12.989
Well, what do you know?

41:12.991 --> 41:15.396
I must be, uh, growing on them after all.

41:17.567 --> 41:19.201
[Donna] <i>Hey, guys, uh, okay,
set lists are now available...</i>

41:19.203 --> 41:21.072
Christ on a bike!

41:21.074 --> 41:24.178
[Donna] <i>...production
office. Come and get 'em.</i>

41:24.180 --> 41:25.515
Mr. Diligence.

41:25.517 --> 41:28.621
[Reignwolf] <i>♪ Are
you satisfied? ♪</i>

41:28.623 --> 41:31.627
[band playing blues rock music]

41:31.629 --> 41:33.697
<i>♪♪♪</i>

41:33.699 --> 41:37.404
<i>♪ Hey there's nowhere to go ♪</i>

41:37.406 --> 41:42.414
<i>♪♪♪</i>

41:42.416 --> 41:45.287
<i>♪ I've been paralyzed ♪</i>

41:45.289 --> 41:46.723
<i>♪ Ohh ♪</i>

41:46.725 --> 41:51.633
<i>♪♪♪</i>

41:51.635 --> 41:53.737
Hey! Hey!

41:53.739 --> 41:55.407
Whoa, w-w-what is
it? W-what's wrong?

41:55.409 --> 41:56.577
No, please don't say
anything because nothing...

41:56.579 --> 41:57.946
Is this... is this the teleprompter?

41:57.948 --> 41:59.248
- ...nothing that you...
- Look, you just

41:59.250 --> 42:00.651
- gotta let it...
- Just...

42:00.653 --> 42:02.120
Ahh.

42:02.122 --> 42:03.958
- Oh, say, Reg, did you get a...
- What?

42:03.960 --> 42:06.028
Did you get a chance to mention it?

42:06.030 --> 42:07.532
What I spoke to you about earlier?

42:07.534 --> 42:09.134
Oh, what, you mean the
finger kissing thing?

42:09.136 --> 42:10.605
- Yeah.
- No, no, there wasn't time

42:10.607 --> 42:12.374
because, you see, I was
too busy trying to convince

42:12.376 --> 42:13.978
your mate Chris not to fire me.

42:13.980 --> 42:15.413
So it looks like you're gonna

42:15.415 --> 42:16.617
have to tell him yourself after all.

42:16.619 --> 42:19.088
Well, Reg, just so you know,

42:19.090 --> 42:21.092
I never told Christopher
he should fire you.

42:21.094 --> 42:22.294
I know. I know.

42:22.296 --> 42:24.131
I know 'cause I know who did.

42:24.133 --> 42:27.004
So, oh, you know, if we consolidate, um,

42:27.006 --> 42:29.108
some of these cases, we
can eliminate one coach.

42:29.110 --> 42:30.678
You know the one with
the discarded set pieces?

42:30.680 --> 42:33.149
- The old sets?
- That way, we wouldn't need

42:33.151 --> 42:36.155
to let anybody else go.

42:36.157 --> 42:38.827
[whistles upbeat melody]

42:38.829 --> 42:43.269
<i>♪♪♪</i>

42:43.271 --> 42:46.843
<i>♪ Are you satisfied? ♪</i>

42:46.845 --> 42:51.855
<i>♪♪♪</i>

42:55.630 --> 42:56.463
[Christopher trilling]

42:56.465 --> 42:58.399
[knock at door]

42:58.401 --> 43:00.003
- Hey, brother.
- Hey.

43:00.005 --> 43:02.508
How you doing? You look good.

43:02.510 --> 43:03.911
Okay, what's wrong?

43:03.913 --> 43:06.415
Well... [clears throat]

43:06.417 --> 43:09.355
...I think we should just
walk to the stage in silence.

43:09.357 --> 43:12.027
I-I mean, it's not like anything
I say is gonna help, you know?

43:12.029 --> 43:14.033
Yes, in silence! Great.

43:15.035 --> 43:18.707
Like Phil always did it.

43:18.709 --> 43:21.813
Yeah, exactly. Like Phil did it.

43:21.815 --> 43:23.951
And you know the thing with the...

43:23.953 --> 43:25.454
...with your fingers?

43:25.456 --> 43:27.458
- I do that?
- You know you do.

43:27.460 --> 43:29.996
Is it, uh, is it pissing Tom off?

43:29.998 --> 43:31.833
[chuckles] You know it is.

43:31.835 --> 43:33.403
[laughs] So what about it?

43:33.405 --> 43:34.839
Well...

43:34.841 --> 43:37.044
Bill, before I forget,

43:37.046 --> 43:39.584
that toilet's clogged.

43:41.822 --> 43:43.757
I'll take care of it.

43:43.759 --> 43:44.859
Excuse me.

43:44.861 --> 43:46.897
I'll shut this so you can...

43:46.899 --> 43:48.435
[knock at door]

43:50.372 --> 43:54.445
Hey, just need you to approve the set list.

43:54.447 --> 43:57.117
Oh, and, uh, Tom wants these
three songs on the teleprompter.

43:57.119 --> 43:58.587
[toilet water clogging]

43:58.589 --> 44:01.893
- That okay?
- Whatever Tom wants.

44:01.895 --> 44:02.762
Great. Thanks.

44:02.764 --> 44:04.833
[Bill] <i>Shit. Shit!</i>

44:04.835 --> 44:06.636
Is there someone in your bathroom?

44:06.638 --> 44:08.172
- Oh, just Bill.
- [Bill] <i>So much water!</i>

44:08.174 --> 44:09.676
- Dealing with a clog.
- [Bill] <i>Everywhere.</i>

44:09.678 --> 44:11.880
- Game on.
- [Bill] <i>Come on.</i>

44:11.882 --> 44:15.019
I'm gonna hand these out
and then I'll be back.

44:15.021 --> 44:18.392
[performing vocal exercises]

44:18.394 --> 44:20.163
Guys, here you go.

44:20.165 --> 44:22.367
Patience is a virtue.

44:22.369 --> 44:24.271
Kelly Ann?

44:24.273 --> 44:26.943
"Coyote Kisses," "How It Fades,"

44:26.945 --> 44:28.714
"Miss Begotten."

44:28.716 --> 44:30.684
Wait a second. Wait!

44:30.686 --> 44:32.688
I need the lyrics.

44:32.690 --> 44:33.757
The Blue and The Black website.

44:33.759 --> 44:35.628
It has every Staton-House lyric.

44:35.630 --> 44:37.297
Right, yeah.

44:37.299 --> 44:40.303
[muffled rock music plays over headphones]

44:40.305 --> 44:45.315
<i>♪♪♪</i>

44:52.229 --> 44:53.463
[knocks softly]

44:53.465 --> 44:55.469
[whispers] It's me.

44:57.607 --> 44:59.576
[sighs]

44:59.578 --> 45:01.646
Well, the good news is,

45:01.648 --> 45:04.552
these T-shirts, they're really absorbent.

45:04.554 --> 45:06.523
The bad news is...

45:06.525 --> 45:08.226
[clears throat] ...I'm dying.

45:08.228 --> 45:10.564
I had my blood pressure checked.

45:10.566 --> 45:12.969
Uh, it... it scared a nurse.

45:12.971 --> 45:14.939
Of course your blood pressure's high.

45:14.941 --> 45:18.914
You drink 18 espressos and
wash it down with Bullet Coffee.

45:18.916 --> 45:20.416
I'll do this.

45:20.418 --> 45:22.889
It's time to walk 'em to the stage,

45:22.891 --> 45:24.659
as only you can.

45:24.661 --> 45:27.465
Why'd he have to leave?

45:27.467 --> 45:30.436
I fucking miss him.

45:30.438 --> 45:31.506
Your dad?

45:31.508 --> 45:33.944
No, Phil. Fucking Phil.

45:33.946 --> 45:37.687
I don't miss my dad... that often.

45:40.158 --> 45:45.133
I can't fill Phil's shoes.

45:45.135 --> 45:46.538
Just be you.

45:48.341 --> 45:52.848
So... I know why The Head and
The Heart were so pissed off.

45:52.850 --> 45:55.219
Milo accused them of
drawing Dirty Sanchezes

45:55.221 --> 45:56.890
on Rick's Potato Heads.

45:56.892 --> 45:58.292
They didn't do it.

45:58.294 --> 45:59.462
It was Winston.

45:59.464 --> 46:02.635
- The devil child?
- Mm-hmm.

46:02.637 --> 46:04.071
You really are Nancy Drew.

46:04.073 --> 46:06.077
[laughs]

46:09.985 --> 46:14.826
You know, Double D suggested
that we send back that truck

46:14.828 --> 46:17.698
that has the old set on it to save money.

46:17.700 --> 46:20.003
Fuck. That's actually a good idea.

46:20.005 --> 46:22.508
Yeah, I know.

46:22.510 --> 46:23.977
- Fuck him.
- Mm-hmm.

46:23.979 --> 46:25.279
- Fuck 'em all.
- Mmm.

46:25.281 --> 46:28.520
Get out there. I got this.

46:28.522 --> 46:30.457
<i>[pensive rock music]</i>

46:30.459 --> 46:34.197
I can't believe I've been
co-opted into teleprompting.

46:34.199 --> 46:36.669
It's inauthentic.

46:36.671 --> 46:39.174
It's false.

46:39.176 --> 46:41.078
Copy that one.

46:41.080 --> 46:43.683
- [computer chimes]
- I really appreciate this.

46:43.685 --> 46:46.589
I know.

46:46.591 --> 46:48.727
Look, I was emotionally prepared for you

46:48.729 --> 46:50.664
not to be here anymore, so...

46:50.666 --> 46:52.735
No, I-I get it.

46:52.737 --> 46:57.547
So now you're back, it's
just hard to even look at you.

47:00.619 --> 47:04.525
Oh, this song... makes me cry.

47:04.527 --> 47:09.201
I mean, you were my best friend
on this tour, besides Milo.

47:09.203 --> 47:11.573
- I was?
- We gave you a pie.

47:11.575 --> 47:13.510
And with that pie,

47:13.512 --> 47:17.585
I symbolically severed myself from you.

47:17.587 --> 47:20.323
Yeah, I mean, it makes... it makes sense.

47:20.325 --> 47:22.928
Lose the songwriter credits.

47:22.930 --> 47:25.834
I mean, I still love you,

47:25.836 --> 47:27.571
but you're not getting your bunk back.

47:27.573 --> 47:29.509
<i>♪ Then I laughed and I said ♪</i>

47:29.511 --> 47:31.613
<i>♪ Oh silly me, that's just me ♪</i>

47:31.615 --> 47:36.021
<i>♪ Then I proceeded to not
comb some stranger's hair ♪</i>

47:36.023 --> 47:37.290
<i>♪ Never was my style ♪</i>

47:37.292 --> 47:38.292
- [gasps]
- [computer chimes]

47:38.294 --> 47:40.129
<i>♪♪♪</i>

47:40.131 --> 47:41.933
I fucking did it!

47:41.935 --> 47:43.235
<i>♪ But I couldn't tell you ♪</i>

47:43.237 --> 47:44.772
Yeah!

47:44.774 --> 47:46.876
<i>♪ What the hell it
was supposed to mean ♪</i>

47:46.878 --> 47:49.749
<i>♪ 'Cause it was a
Monday, no, Tuesday ♪</i>

47:49.751 --> 47:52.320
<i>♪ No, Wednesday,
Thursday, Friday ♪</i>

47:52.322 --> 47:55.460
<i>♪ Then Saturday came
around and I said ♪</i>

47:55.462 --> 47:58.767
<i>♪ Who's this stupid clown
blocking the bathroom sink? ♪</i>

47:58.769 --> 48:00.336
<i>♪♪♪</i>

48:00.338 --> 48:01.338
Hi.

48:01.340 --> 48:02.641
<i>♪ All my clothes ♪</i>

48:02.643 --> 48:04.745
<i>♪ I gotta say pretty pimpin' ♪</i>

48:04.747 --> 48:09.757
<i>♪♪♪</i>

48:14.066 --> 48:17.072
[raucous cheers and applause]

48:23.050 --> 48:26.221
Woo-hoo! Whoo!

48:26.223 --> 48:29.227
[triumphant music plays over loudspeakers]

48:29.229 --> 48:30.631
<i>♪♪♪</i>

48:30.633 --> 48:31.966
Hey!

48:31.968 --> 48:34.672
You gotta stop with the...

48:34.674 --> 48:36.609
No more.

48:36.611 --> 48:39.749
Yeah, you're right, Bill.

48:39.751 --> 48:41.351
You always tell me the truth.

48:41.353 --> 48:43.625
I try.

48:47.533 --> 48:50.539
[cheers and applause continue]

48:52.977 --> 48:54.979
Good show, dude.

48:54.981 --> 48:58.822
[crowd screaming]

